The People of the State of Illinois, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Francis Baker, Defendant-Appellant.(No. 58354;First District (5th Division)February 15, 1974.

DRUCKER, J., took no part.

James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago (Shelvin Singer, Professor of Law, I.I.T. Chicago-Kent College of Law, of counsel), for appellant.Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Kenneth L. Gillis and Lee T. Hettinger, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People. PER CURIAM.
